<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900619-0149</DOCNO><DOCID>900619-0149.</DOCID><HL>   Southern Mineral to Post Gain</HL><DATE>06/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SMIN PPW</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><LP>   HOUSTON -- Southern Mineral Corp. said it expects torecord a $5.7 million second-quarter gain from the sale ofits interests in an oil and natural gas field in Mississippi.   In the year-earlier second quarter, the energy explorationconcern had net income of $337,000, or eight cents a share,on revenue of $850,000.</LP><TEXT>   Southern Mineral said it sold its interests in the TrimbleField, which is in the Smith and Simpson counties ofMississippi, to Nerco Oil andamp; Gas Co. for $10.8 million. Nercois a unit of PacifiCorp of Portland, Ore.</TEXT></DOC>